---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'San Marino Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/san-marino/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Italy for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/italy' },
  { title: 'Monaco for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/monaco' },
  { title: 'Croatia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/croatia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'sanMarinoFit', header: 'San Marino Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€400-570/mo', sanMarinoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€465-665/mo', sanMarinoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€360-515/mo', sanMarinoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€335-480/mo', sanMarinoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'ISS (San Marino)', entryAge: 'All ages', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: '€150-250/mo', sanMarinoFit: 'Required' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'ISS (Mandatory)', monthly: '€150-250', annual: '€1,800-3,000' },
  { category: 'Private Supplement (65-69)', monthly: '€335-570', annual: '€4,020-6,840' },
  { category: 'Private Supplement (70-74)', monthly: '€460-760', annual: '€5,520-9,120' },
  { category: 'Private Supplement (75-79)', monthly: '€615-1,020', annual: '€7,380-12,240' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit (Italy)', monthly: '€80-150/visit', annual: 'As needed' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in San Marino 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in San Marino. Historic microstate, Italian access, lower taxes, and coverage for retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in San Marino"
  subheadline="San Marino offers ancient republic charm, Italian culture access, lower taxes than Italy, hilltop views, and unique citizenship—a historic microstate surrounded by Italy for Italophile retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/san-marino-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose San Marino</h2>
  <p>
    San Marino offers the world's oldest republic, stunning hilltop location, Italian culture without Italian taxes, and unique prestige as a microstate. For Italophile retirees seeking lower taxes while enjoying Italian lifestyle, San Marino provides a distinctive alternative to mainland Italy.
  </p>

  <p>
    San Marino city is the capital on Mount Titano. Borgo Maggiore is below the cliff. Serravalle is the largest municipality. Rimini (Italy) is 20 minutes away with beach, airport, and hospitals. Population only 34,000. Very intimate community.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> State Hospital; Italian hospitals accessible</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Italian</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,000-3,500/month; similar to Italy</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean-continental; mild</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Historic; quiet; Italian influenced</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> Lower than Italy; max 35% income tax</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">San Marino Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    San Marino has ISS (Istituto per la Sicurezza Sociale)—state healthcare system covering residents. San Marino State Hospital provides basic care. Agreements with Italy allow access to Italian hospitals—Ospedale Infermi Rimini is 20 minutes away. Bologna hospitals 1.5 hours. Healthcare limited locally but Italian backup excellent.
  </p>

  <p>
    ISS is mandatory social security covering healthcare. Private insurance supplements for faster access and Italian private clinics. Italian public hospitals accessible through agreements.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">ISS Is Mandatory</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      All San Marino residents must enroll in ISS social security. Covers state healthcare. Italian hospitals accessible through agreements. Private insurance supplements for private clinics and faster access. Budget for both ISS and private coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    San Marino residency options:
  </p>

  <h3>Residency Permit</h3>
  <p>
    Requires proof of income, housing, and good character. Financial requirements (typically €30,000+/year income). Apply through San Marino authorities. Not automatic—approval required.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership</h3>
  <p>
    Buying property can support residency application. Real estate investment shows commitment.
  </p>

  <h3>Processing</h3>
  <p>
    Apply through San Marino Secretariat of State. Background checks conducted. Small state so individual consideration. Processing 3-6 months typically.
  </p>

  <h3>Note on Access</h3>
  <p>
    San Marino is surrounded by Italy—you'll transit Italy constantly. Schengen access needed for practical living.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for San Marino:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>ISS:</strong> Mandatory for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Private:</strong> Recommended for comprehensive access</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage:</strong> Should include Italy</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage useful</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for San Marino</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      ISS (mandatory) plus private international insurance. Private coverage should include Italy for Rimini and Bologna hospitals. Consider European coverage since San Marino residents typically travel in EU regularly.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in San Marino, Italian and European coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for San Marino</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong European network, Italy access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Italian hospitals:</strong> Rimini and Bologna excellent</li>
    <li><strong>ISS supplement:</strong> Covers private options</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for San Marino with Italy access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for San Marino (EUR):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Total Healthcare Budget</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ISS + Private:</strong> €500-820/month typical</li>
    <li><strong>Tax advantage:</strong> Lower than Italy for high earners</li>
    <li><strong>Italian access:</strong> Excellent backup nearby</li>
    <li><strong>Reasonable costs:</strong> Not Monaco-level expensive</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Italian Escapee, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €4,000/month pension. Former Milan resident. Tax optimization.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> ISS + Cigna Global with Italy coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€600/month total. Tax savings; Italian lifestyle maintained.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: History Enthusiast, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €3,500/month. US citizen. Unique republic appeal.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> ISS + BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€700/month total. Historic setting; excellent backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Beach & Mountain, 65</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,800/month. Serravalle residence. Rimini beach access.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> ISS + Allianz Care regional.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€520/month total. Hilltop living; coastal getaways.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What are the tax advantages?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Lower than Italy—income tax tops at 35% vs Italy's 43%. No wealth tax. Capital gains rates favorable. For high earners moving from Italy, savings significant. Professional tax advice essential.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use Italian hospitals?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—agreements with Italy allow access. ISS covers some costs; private insurance ensures full access to Italian private clinics. Rimini excellent; Bologna for complex cases.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is San Marino boring?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very quiet—34,000 population, hilltop location. Beautiful but limited entertainment. Rimini beach 20 minutes. Bologna culture 1.5 hours. Best for those seeking peace and views over nightlife.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Italian visa?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Practical necessity—San Marino surrounded by Italy. Need ability to transit Italy regularly. San Marino residency doesn't grant Schengen rights. May need both San Marino residency and Schengen visa depending on nationality.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for San Marino coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. San Marino residency requirements change. Note that San Marino residency doesn't grant EU/Schengen access—separate arrangements needed for Italy transit. Consult with professional advisors.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
